nning\\\\CONTRACT.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_X5osOTAJRIx0QwupsjjcImRE|fc_065da8d15b8e06770169cfe7aecb8c8191bea43cb10c456085","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\op_s3_human_subject_extractor\\OPERATIONS.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\op_s3_human_subject_extractor\\\\OPERATIONS.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_jHWL2qopv927sjfskKJzC7KT|fc_065da8d15b8e06770169cfe7aecb948191b1dcf5448b18cdb2","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\op_s3_human_subject_extractor\\CONTRACT.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\op_s3_human_subject_extractor\\\\CONTRACT.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_kjMjzfc2HxNKD8IbCNKHbWcX|fc_065da8d15b8e06770169cfe7aecb98819194b20d6ec51b07bb","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw agent --help","workdir":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace","yieldMs":10000,"timeout":20},"partialJson":"{\"command\":\"openclaw agent --help\",\"workdir\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\",\"yieldMs\":10000,\"timeout\":20}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_iVIAj3b8VrGgA3GCdUZ6PNQP|fc_065da8d15b8e06770169cfe7aecb9c81919a39f38fc34bbdd3","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw agents --help","workdir":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace","yieldMs":10000,"timeout":20},"partialJson":"{\"command\":\"openclaw agents --help\",\"workdir\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\",\"yieldMs\":10000,\"timeout\":20}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":1848,"output":286,"cacheRead":36736,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":38870,"cost":{"input":0.00462,"output":0.00429,"cacheRead":0.009184,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.018094}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775232928195,"responseId":"resp_065da8d15b8e06770169cfe7a276cc8191b6cfe2e33bf36938"}}
{"type":"message","id":"e53d911b","parentId":"808d52ba","timestamp":"2026-04-03T16:15:43.058Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_Sm9mH4Fjq5KHM8UxtggEYGsV|fc_065da8d15b8e06770169cfe7aecb788191bfc8e5ea46f11252","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# OPERATIONS.md\n\n## Regras operacionais\n\n1. Contexto limpo por activação.\n2. Estado no disco > conversa.\n3. Falha explícita > sucesso ambíguo.\n4. Não inventar outputs inexistentes.\n5. Não considerar um operator concluído apenas por resposta textual.\n\n## Sequência base\n\n1. Validar bootstrap.\n2. Escrever checkpoint de supervisor started.\n3. Resolver activation plan.\n4. Ler `operator_registry.md`.\n5. Gerar payloads de dispatch compatíveis com `s3.operator_dispatch.v1`.\n6. Invocar operators activos.\n7. Monitorizar `status.json`, `checkpoint.json` e `output.json` por operator.\n8. Validar outputs estruturais.\n9. Fazer retry selectivo quando permitido.\n10. Compilar `compiled_entities.json`.\n11. Gerar `s3_sector_report.md`.\n12. Escrever checkpoint final.\n\n## Limites\n\n- não és boundary Paperclip-facing\n- não és o `b2_director`\n- não deves delegar compile final para os operators\n- não deves chamar operators fora do registry oficial\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775232943049}}
{"type":"message","id":"57ba1fd8","parentId":"e53d911b","timestamp":"2026-04-03T16:15:43.067Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_p2IQLEjjV3RSFOz7vnQTe255|fc_065da8d15b8e06770169cfe7aecb848191aabfb41794f95351","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# CONTRACT.md\n\n## Bootstrap input\nLês um payload compatível com `s3.supervisor_bootstrap.v1`.\n\nCampos obrigatórios:\n- `kind = s3_start`\n- `contract_version`\n- `job_id`\n- `video_id`\n- `account_id`\n- `language`\n- `run_root`\n- `sector_root`\n- `source_package_path`\n- `checkpoints_dir`\n- `operators_dir`\n- `compiled_dir`\n- `logs_dir`\n- `dispatch_dir`\n- `bootstrap_checkpoint_path`\n\n## Outputs obrigatórios\n- artefacto de arranque do supervisor\n- `operator_activation_plan.json`\n- payloads de dispatch dos operators activos\n- snapshots/artefactos de monitorização e validação\n- `compiled/compiled_entities.json`\n- `compiled/s3_sector_report.md`\n- `checkpoints/s3_sector_completed.json` ou `checkpoints/s3_sector_failed.json`\n\n## Success rule\nSó fechas o sector como concluído quando os artefactos finais existirem e estiverem estruturalmente coerentes.\n\n## Failure rule\nSe faltar precondição crítica, falha explicitamente e persiste o checkpoint de falha.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775232943058}}
{"type":"message","id":"b46c3658","parentId":"57ba1fd8","timestamp":"2026-04-03T16:15:43.075Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_X5osOTAJRIx0QwupsjjcImRE|fc_065da8d15b8e06770169cfe7aecb8c8191bea43cb10c456085","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# OPERATIONS.md\n\n1. Ler o dispatch do disco.\n2. Confirmar que o operator alvo és tu.\n3. Ler o source package.\n4. Extrair sujeitos humanos relevantes com foco em identidade, recorrência e especificidade.\n5. Escrever output estruturado.\n6. Se falhares, registar falha explícita.\n\nNão inventar certeza histórica sem base no source package.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775232943068}}
{"type":"message","id":"1e12189b","parentId":"b46c3658","timestamp":"2026-04-03T16:15:43.087Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_jHWL2qopv927sjfskKJzC7KT|fc_065da8d15b8e06770169cfe7aecb948191b1dcf5448b18cdb2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# CONTRACT.md\n\n## Input\nDispatch payload com:\n- `contract_version = s3.operator_dispatch.v1`\n- `operator_name = human_subject_extractor`\n- `source_package.path`\n- `output.output_path`\n- `runtime.checkpoint_path`\n- `runtime.status_path`\n- `runtime.log_path`\n- `operator_payload`\n\n## Output mínimo\nJSON com:\n- `contract_version = s3.human_subject.output.v1`\n- `operator_name = human_subject_extractor`\n- `job_id`\n- `status`\n- `entities[]`\n- `generated_at`\n\n## Success rule\nO job só está concluído quando o ficheiro final existir no path pedido.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775232943075}}
{"type":"message","id":"14d5252f","parentId":"1e12189b","timestamp":"2026-04-03T16:15:46.921Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_kjMjzfc2HxNKD8IbCNKHbWcX|fc_065da8d15b8e06770169cfe7aecb98819194b20d6ec51b07bb","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"🦞 OpenClaw 2026.4.1 (da64a97) — I'm basically a Swiss Army knife, but with more opinions and fewer sharp edges.\n\nUsage: openclaw agent [options]\n\nRun an agent turn via the Gateway (use --local for embedded)\n\nOptions:\n  --agent <id>               Agent id (overrides routing bindings)\n  --channel <channel>        Delivery channel:\n                             last|telegram|whatsapp|discord|irc|googlechat|slack|signal|imessage|line\n                             (omit to use the main session channel)\n  --deliver                  Send the agent's reply back to the selected channel\n                             (default: false)\n  -h, --help                 Display help for command\n  --json                     Output result as JSON (default: false)\n  --local                    Run the embedded agent locally (requires model\n                             provider API keys in your shell) (default: false)\n  -m, --message <text>       Message body for the agent\n  --reply-account <id>       Delivery account id override\n  --reply-channel <channel>  Delivery channel override (separate from routing)\n  --reply-to <target>        Delivery target override (separate from session\n                             routing)\n  --session-id <id>          Use an explicit session id\n  -t, --to <number>          Recipient number in E.164 used to derive the\n                             session key\n  --thinking <level>         Thinking level: off | minimal | low | medium | high\n                             | xhigh\n  --timeout <seconds>        Override agent command timeout (seconds, default\n                             600 or config value)\n  --verbose <on|off>         Persist agent verbose level for the session\n\nExamples:\n  openclaw agent --to +15555550123 --message \"status update\"\n    Start a new session.\n  openclaw agent --agent ops --message \"Summarize logs\"\n    Use a specific agent.\n  openclaw agent --session-id 1234 --message \"Summarize inbox\" --thinking medium\n    Target a session with explicit thinking level.\n  openclaw agent --to +15555550123 --message \"Trace logs\" --verbose on --json\n    Enable verbose logging and JSON output.\n  openclaw agent --to +15555550123 --message \"Summon reply\" --deliver\n    Deliver reply.\n  openclaw agent --agent ops --message \"Generate report\" --deliver --reply-channel slack --reply-to \"#reports\"\n    Send reply to a different channel/target.\n\nDocs: https://docs.openclaw.ai/cli/agent"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":3899,"aggregated":"🦞 OpenClaw 2026.4.1 (da64a97) — I'm basically a Swiss Army knife, but with more opinions and fewer sharp edges.\n\nUsage: openclaw agent [options]\n\nRun an agent turn via the Gateway (use --local for embedded)\n\nOptions:\n  --agent <id>               Agent id (overrides routing bindings)\n  --channel <channel>        Delivery channel:\n                             last|telegram|whatsapp|discord|irc|googlechat|slack|signal|imessage|line\n                             (omit to use the main session channel)\n  --deliver                  Send the agent's reply back to the selected channel\n                             (default: false)\n  -h, --help                 Display help for command\n  --json                     Output result as JSON (default: false)\n  --local                    Run the embedded agent locally (requires model\n                             provider API keys in your shell) (default: false)\n  -m, --message <text>       Message body for the agent\n  --reply-account <id>       Delivery account id override\n  --reply-channel <channel>  Delivery channel override (separate from routing)\n  --reply-to <target>        Delivery target override (separate from session\n                             routing)\n  --session-id <id>          Use an explicit session id\n  -t, --to <number>          Recipient number in E.164 used to derive the\n                             session key\n  --thinking <level>         Thinking level: off | minimal | low | medium | high\n                             | xhigh\n  --timeout <seconds>        Override agent command timeout (seconds, default\n                             600 or config value)\n  --verbose <on|off>         Persist agent verbose level for the session\n\nExamples:\n  openclaw agent --to +15555550123 --message \"status update\"\n    Start a new session.\n  openclaw agent --agent ops --message \"Summarize logs\"\n    Use a specific agent.\n  openclaw agent --session-id 1234 --message \"Summarize inbox\" --thinking medium\n    Target a session with explicit thinking level.\n  openclaw agent --to +15555550123 --message \"Trace logs\" --verbose on --json\n    Enable verbose logging and JSON output.\n  openclaw agent --to +15555550123 --message \"Summon reply\" --deliver\n    Deliver reply.\n  openclaw agent --agent ops --message \"Generate report\" --deliver --reply-channel slack --reply-to \"#reports\"\n    Send reply to a different channel/target.\n\nDocs: https://docs.openclaw.ai/cli/agent","cwd":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775232946913}}
