{"type":"message","id":"64fae965","parentId":"c089c5b3","timestamp":"2026-04-03T16:23:13.531Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Creating validation notes**\n\nI think it could be helpful to add a document summarizing validation processes and any blockers, even though it might not be strictly necessary. A concise note would be useful, so I'll create it in the content factory block. I’m thinking of naming it `REAL_RUN_VALIDATION_2026-04-03.md`. That way, anyone who looks at it later will have a clear understanding of the validations we've done and any issues we encountered. Let’s get started on that!","thinkingSignature":"{\"id\":\"rs_065da8d15b8e06770169cfe95823c081919f504ced96c9ac37\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABpz-lcli9ot3-QEZm3kqdnKnraNtWXI1SbpSbhqNLuBj-RHcCnNq1dPWChvi4wDTCR-xFUZvuOGY6P5_vUDu6P85i94lW0donDAdxdMGQT6arPzgHdkOH8TIEoP8cRgr5v9rL5ysSr_z6_F4Ac-fwPaGnw5s3C1ugppDoIX4IXgooQKkaqYHTSyHrVhg2yhaI9Bo7fhN417O18q0AWzsa1AgRj9owJTs5v61Bq3J2BPMgOMusIbc3cbz_v3uYPY37f6SnrJe9MIvgLCkF7Cg-eiH1uj_EFSYW1amK_q6pVQbmFT47vkiUr7AQHjurLLWzW8yks9yUkFJf3Oq845OC9l-odgYuVKQ_5wScISSS0z5EJmlpjivUuDLokLznvPP6b0Q304t9iGNXD35QiWdCzKgp-j8VIN4yyKNd2CDfOtAt2WF7ZLNQoSOpOHgEkyh_XIZW6mpdVeJljTab7hyAz3McFXOLBzi21beingYAtUtLriXHKFQuvCLKzFNQcZzq20VsLIdjQl6_yC072CNJcF3SPQ6ZPuiNiXOEv3iO0ejMZyJKkmj_W7wV6-bYeB1uInHw-Jy_N9mKFY2W-nd7j8NVnPSF8foZfGKSPJRS466PssAdAMbdzZv7fMGsuA4nvitLHUB9ElxhC6nyVSPfrdtsGlw6Y92W7tQfUwn_5EPnrOyPeJ560sjmJJTmjkg6KS3tY6xVfaEx51nKuJQNZZRCXL9RM4dki-IWc7BIOaonCiNiHmZjCG_EX4AEIsreEaTKsIRzQtSwrWzGJUZphR6dfCiKZyMnku92bM_XxbhVjL9hjaV54n3BdlNJxsXc7Bs1jPEeTNBw7MebDqsdiwVWh6QATLo11ijl0kob64o5xgL3RYQTifh2GRjQ7RKmPRg6dBUfNy04vJ55hb1Nz8Ml74e8n4Ni7Fu3hqayPPEqRQDJY4rDOh3hJSzpqHmV_Y5IbVtUmOmQZ8UavN_a3schPlAGHQMemjkQ4fGHiOw7eaDyhRofwZZ8ME8tdOBYVisBasyFQSGn-cEsvpXnQb9b8f9c7oWGwiX51877lMz7rH08AH89aVZLWzF1Y05zZ5a3IhAFXq7inNQiAGg9ClcQB1CmMAijThAvHJ-Om0kiJRzw=\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Creating validation notes**\\n\\nI think it could be helpful to add a document summarizing validation processes and any blockers, even though it might not be strictly necessary. A concise note would be useful, so I'll create it in the content factory block. I’m thinking of naming it `REAL_RUN_VALIDATION_2026-04-03.md`. That way, anyone who looks at it later will have a clear understanding of the validations we've done and any issues we encountered. Let’s get started on that!\"}]}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_fbMNP0CMDe8G4ewLtbxwM6aL|fc_065da8d15b8e06770169cfe95c97088191a295238ac75f80b8","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\REAL_RUN_VALIDATION_2026-04-03.md","content":"# Real Run Validation — 2026-04-03\n\n## Goal\nValidate the next execution tranche for Block 2 with a real OpenClaw path narrower than the full sector: bootstrap B2/S3 correctly, run at least one real S3 operator agent, validate its output structurally, compile sector artifacts, and observe what still blocks Paperclip/Perseus activation of `b2_director -> S3`.\n\n## What was changed\n\n### 1. `helpers/build_s3_bootstrap_from_b2.py`\nUpgraded the generated `s3_source_package.json` so it now mirrors the shape documented in `S3/inputs.md` much more closely:\n- reads `screenplay_analysis.json`\n- optionally reads `01_script_fetched.json`\n- writes `video_context`\n- writes `script_overview`\n- writes normalized `scenes[]`\n- preserves `entity_focus` and upstream input references\n\n### 2. `S3/helpers/build_operator_dispatches.py`\nAdded narrow-run support:\n- can now emit dispatches for all operators\n- or for one selected operator only\n- writes an activation plan that explicitly marks the inactive operators\n\n### 3. `helpers/real_run_b2_s3_one_operator.py`\nAdded a mechanical validation runner that:\n- creates an isolated run root\n- bootstraps B2 in `s3_only`\n- builds canonical S3 bootstrap + source package\n- generates dispatch for one selected operator\n- invokes the real OpenClaw operator agent via `openclaw agent --agent ...`\n- validates operator output against schema\n- compiles `compiled_entities.json`\n- generates `s3_sector_report.md`\n- **does not claim block success when the compiled sector status is only `degraded_completed`**\n- emits `s3_failed.json` instead in that narrow-run case\n\n## What is now proven\n\n### Proven mechanically\n1. The real S3 operator agents exist in OpenClaw and are registered:\n   - `op_s3_human_subject_extractor`\n   - `op_s3_environment_location_extractor`\n   - `op_s3_object_artifact_extractor`\n   - `op_s3_symbolic_event_extractor`\n   - plus `sm_s3_visual_planning`\n\n2. A real operator invocation works end-to-end through OpenClaw:\n   - tested agent: `op_s3_human_subject_extractor`\n   - invocation path: `openclaw agent --agent op_s3_human_subject_extractor --message ...`\n   - the agent wrote:\n     - `output.json`\n     - `status.json`\n     - `checkpoint.json`\n\n3. The human operator output passed structural validation against the formal schema.\n\n4. The sector can be compiled from real operator output plus missing-operator gaps, producing:\n   - `compiled/compiled_entities.json`\n   - `compiled/s3_sector_report.md`\n\n5. The system can correctly distinguish:\n   - real operator success\n   - sector compile still being incomplete/degraded\n   - therefore block not actually ready for success closure\n\n### Proven artefact example\nNarrow real run:\n- `runtime_realcheck/run_004/`\n\nKey outputs:\n- `b2/sectors/s3_visual_planning/inputs/s3_source_package.json`\n- `b2/sectors/s3_visual_planning/checkpoints/operator_activation_plan.json`\n- `b2/sectors/s3_visual_planning/dispatch/human_subject_extractor_job.json`\n- `b2/sectors/s3_visual_planning/operators/human_subject_extractor/output.json`\n- `b2/sectors/s3_visual_planning/compiled/compiled_entities.json`\n- `b2/checkpoints/s3_failed.json`\n\n## What is still not proven\n\n1. **`b2_director` itself is not yet proven as a real invoked agent turn.**\n   The current validation used helpers to simulate the director’s mechanical responsibilities instead of invoking a real `b2_director` agent turn and observing it make the transition itself.\n\n2. **`sm_s3_visual_planning` itself is not yet proven as a real invoked supervisor turn.**\n   The current narrow run used helper scripts to prepare dispatch, then invoked one real operator directly.\n\n3. **The full S3 happy path with all required operators is not yet proven.**\n   The compile status for the narrow run is `degraded_completed`, not `completed`.\n\n4. **Resume semantics back into the director are not yet proven with a real agent turn.**\n   We have the checkpoints and helper logic, but not an observed real re-entry of `b2_director` on `s3_completed` / `s3_failed`.\n\n5. **Paperclip -> Perseus -> b2_director activation is not yet proven operationally.**\n   No live Paperclip-facing trigger was exercised here.\n\n## Current blocker statement for Perseus\nPaperclip should **not** yet assume that creating Perseus is enough to activate a coherent `b2_director -> S3` runtime.\n\nWhy:\n- the real operator layer is partially proven\n- the source-package + dispatch substrate is stronger now\n- but the actual control-plane agents (`b2_director`, `sm_s3_visual_planning`) are still not proven in a live turn-to-turn runtime loop\n- and the full-S3 success condition is still unproven\n\n## Recommended next validation tranche\n1. Invoke **real `sm_s3_visual_planning`** with the generated `s3.supervisor_bootstrap.v1` payload.\n2. Make the supervisor dispatch **only one allowed operator** in a controlled test mode, but own the dispatch itself.\n3. Observe the supervisor writing sector checkpoints itself.\n4. Then invoke **real `b2_director`** on bootstrap and on resume, instead of helper scripts.\n5. Only after those two control-plane agents are proven should Paperclip create Perseus to drive this path.\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\\\\content_factory_block2\\\\REAL_RUN_VALIDATION_2026-04-03.md\",\"content\":\"# Real Run Validation — 2026-04-03\\n\\n## Goal\\nValidate the next execution tranche for Block 2 with a real OpenClaw path narrower than the full sector: bootstrap B2/S3 correctly, run at least one real S3 operator agent, validate its output structurally, compile sector artifacts, and observe what still blocks Paperclip/Perseus activation of `b2_director -> S3`.\\n\\n## What was changed\\n\\n### 1. `helpers/build_s3_bootstrap_from_b2.py`\\nUpgraded the generated `s3_source_package.json` so it now mirrors the shape documented in `S3/inputs.md` much more closely:\\n- reads `screenplay_analysis.json`\\n- optionally reads `01_script_fetched.json`\\n- writes `video_context`\\n- writes `script_overview`\\n- writes normalized `scenes[]`\\n- preserves `entity_focus` and upstream input references\\n\\n### 2. `S3/helpers/build_operator_dispatches.py`\\nAdded narrow-run support:\\n- can now emit dispatches for all operators\\n- or for one selected operator only\\n- writes an activation plan that explicitly marks the inactive operators\\n\\n### 3. `helpers/real_run_b2_s3_one_operator.py`\\nAdded a mechanical validation runner that:\\n- creates an isolated run root\\n- bootstraps B2 in `s3_only`\\n- builds canonical S3 bootstrap + source package\\n- generates dispatch for one selected operator\\n- invokes the real OpenClaw operator agent via `openclaw agent --agent ...`\\n- validates operator output against schema\\n- compiles `compiled_entities.json`\\n- generates `s3_sector_report.md`\\n- **does not claim block success when the compiled sector status is only `degraded_completed`**\\n- emits `s3_failed.json` instead in that narrow-run case\\n\\n## What is now proven\\n\\n### Proven mechanically\\n1. The real S3 operator agents exist in OpenClaw and are registered:\\n   - `op_s3_human_subject_extractor`\\n   - `op_s3_environment_location_extractor`\\n   - `op_s3_object_artifact_extractor`\\n   - `op_s3_symbolic_event_extractor`\\n   - plus `sm_s3_visual_planning`\\n\\n2. A real operator invocation works end-to-end through OpenClaw:\\n   - tested agent: `op_s3_human_subject_extractor`\\n   - invocation path: `openclaw agent --agent op_s3_human_subject_extractor --message ...`\\n   - the agent wrote:\\n     - `output.json`\\n     - `status.json`\\n     - `checkpoint.json`\\n\\n3. The human operator output passed structural validation against the formal schema.\\n\\n4. The sector can be compiled from real operator output plus missing-operator gaps, producing:\\n   - `compiled/compiled_entities.json`\\n   - `compiled/s3_sector_report.md`\\n\\n5. The system can correctly distinguish:\\n   - real operator success\\n   - sector compile still being incomplete/degraded\\n   - therefore block not actually ready for success closure\\n\\n### Proven artefact example\\nNarrow real run:\\n- `runtime_realcheck/run_004/`\\n\\nKey outputs:\\n- `b2/sectors/s3_visual_planning/inputs/s3_source_package.json`\\n- `b2/sectors/s3_visual_planning/checkpoints/operator_activation_plan.json`\\n- `b2/sectors/s3_visual_planning/dispatch/human_subject_extractor_job.json`\\n- `b2/sectors/s3_visual_planning/operators/human_subject_extractor/output.json`\\n- `b2/sectors/s3_visual_planning/compiled/compiled_entities.json`\\n- `b2/checkpoints/s3_failed.json`\\n\\n## What is still not proven\\n\\n1. **`b2_director` itself is not yet proven as a real invoked agent turn.**\\n   The current validation used helpers to simulate the director’s mechanical responsibilities instead of invoking a real `b2_director` agent turn and observing it make the transition itself.\\n\\n2. **`sm_s3_visual_planning` itself is not yet proven as a real invoked supervisor turn.**\\n   The current narrow run used helper scripts to prepare dispatch, then invoked one real operator directly.\\n\\n3. **The full S3 happy path with all required operators is not yet proven.**\\n   The compile status for the narrow run is `degraded_completed`, not `completed`.\\n\\n4. **Resume semantics back into the director are not yet proven with a real agent turn.**\\n   We have the checkpoints and helper logic, but not an observed real re-entry of `b2_director` on `s3_completed` / `s3_failed`.\\n\\n5. **Paperclip -> Perseus -> b2_director activation is not yet proven operationally.**\\n   No live Paperclip-facing trigger was exercised here.\\n\\n## Current blocker statement for Perseus\\nPaperclip should **not** yet assume that creating Perseus is enough to activate a coherent `b2_director -> S3` runtime.\\n\\nWhy:\\n- the real operator layer is partially proven\\n- the source-package + dispatch substrate is stronger now\\n- but the actual control-plane agents (`b2_director`, `sm_s3_visual_planning`) are still not proven in a live turn-to-turn runtime loop\\n- and the full-S3 success condition is still unproven\\n\\n## Recommended next validation tranche\\n1. Invoke **real `sm_s3_visual_planning`** with the generated `s3.supervisor_bootstrap.v1` payload.\\n2. Make the supervisor dispatch **only one allowed operator** in a controlled test mode, but own the dispatch itself.\\n3. Observe the supervisor writing sector checkpoints itself.\\n4. Then invoke **real `b2_director`** on bootstrap and on resume, instead of helper scripts.\\n5. Only after those two control-plane agents are proven should Paperclip create Perseus to drive this path.\\n\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":2909,"output":1407,"cacheRead":64640,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":68956,"cost":{"input":0.0072725,"output":0.021105000000000002,"cacheRead":0.01616,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.04453750000000001}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775233366458,"responseId":"resp_065da8d15b8e06770169cfe956b9d08191889c9d37e904c906"}}
